dc_title_s: The Balkans 1:250,000. Fiume, Susak, sheet Y-12. A.M.S. M506 (G.S.G.S. 4413)
dc_description_s: AMS 2. Great Britain. War Office. General Staff. Geographical Section. G.S.G.S. 4413. Alternate title: Fiume, Susak, Yugoslavia-Italy. Universal transverse Mercator and North Italy zone grids. UTM added, gradient tints and isogonic data deleted by AMS, 1947. Relief shown by 50 and 100 meter contour intervals and and spot elevations. With a Serb and Croat glossary. Corrected from Intelligence reports up to Apr. 1944. Map states location as Yugoslavia/Italy though the map actually depicts Croatia. See index. Library holdings for this set are incomplete.
dc_publisher_s: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, U.S. Army, 1947.
